 blog. After the final installation, I had to make a lot of changes through this template. It had few problems which I had to fix manually. It did not have "Read More" option in the front page posts, so I had to write manual codes to get it fixed. Also top navigation bar was very dull, so worked on it to give some hover effects as well.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Well as of now everything seems to be fine with the template. I would be sticking with this template now. But I noticed one problem here, and that's whenever someone visits the blog for the first time in any browser, the browser asks them their twitter user-name and password. I think this has to be with the twitter updates widget installed in the template. I will be fixing this issue very soon.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Okay, what do you think about this new template of Aslam's BlogBuzz(Now Aslam'sBuzz)?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Do you find any issue with this particular look, if so please let me know your views so that I can work on it to make it more and more better.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;So for now, CiaO ^_^&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/8909909721459519453-7949663533148444013?l=aslam-revised.blogspot.com' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://aslam-revised.blogspot.com/2009/10/aslams-blogbuzz-aslamsbuzz.html</link><author>aslam9895@gmail.com (TechSlam)</author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media='http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/' url='http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_2RdcFsdvQws/SsjX2g4S7FI/AAAAAAAAAyo/A8IGXtcA_R8/s72