ving strong presence worldwide went unnoticed by indian politicians and Indian media, leave apart International media. Anyways few of the media which did show up this news, why was it headlined as "A Mother's Cry" or "A Mobs Punishment". Why the religion of the attackers were not  put under question here? Why?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Here is my view on this, Just because a powerful nation and its government along with its allies is against Islam and its rules, the whole of media turns against Islam and presents Islam as a religion of Terror(Though the fact is that Islam is a religion of Peace, Humanity and Mankind.). Ask any US or Europe citizen who is aware of international news, about the Taliban flogging issue, he will be able to explain how cruel the Taliban is and the Islamic law is. But if you ask him about the similar more barbarious incident that happens in India(Just like the one here about Andhra woman's death), he for most sure will not be aware of this. We cant blame him for that, as International media did not cover this issue as it has nothing to do with Islam or Islamic laws.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Why is this happening, why&amp;nbsp; Islam and its followers are being on target every now and then by the government of many nations and hence of the International media. Don't you think if this Andhra incident had happened in Pakistan or Afghanistan or say Iraq, then I say with full guarantee that it would have been the BREAKING NEWS in almost all International news channels and all around the world people condemning the attack and questioning Islam and its laws.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Crime is crime, no matter which part of the world it occurs. People behind these crimes must be punished be brought behind the judiciary, rather than pointing your fingers against a specific religion, for you have got no right to say a religion preaches terror as all religions stands for Peace, humanity, mankind , love etc.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;My request to all of you is, please wake up, understand how serious the situations are around you, how things are being put in-front of you and how you are made to hate a specific religion or a specific group. my request to all forms of media is go back to the basics of these religions and understand what they stand for, rather than just showing it down as terror group. Remember, by this you are hurting the faith of many out there. Stand for justice and not for those who are in powers. Remember, those who are in powers will never be in power forever, they will comedown as it is said in religious scriptures that, &lt;i&gt;truth will prevail and falsehood is born to perish.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: #b6d7a8;"&gt;Share it with me your views on issues of this kind and the reaction of International media.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/8909909721459519453-7909116123421650131?l=aslam-revised.blogspot.com' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://aslam-revised.blogspot.com/2009/09/biased-international-media.html</link><author>aslam9895@gmail.com (TechSlam)</author><thr:total xmlns:thr='http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0'>2</thr:total></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8909909721459519453.post-8634439727194880198</guid><pubDate>Mon, 31 Aug 2009 15:34:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2009-12-13T18:54:02.877+05:30</atom:updated><category domain='http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#'>Personal Bliss</category><category domain='http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#'>Fun</category><title>ATM  Transaction... How Strange !</title><description>&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Here is the deal.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;I have two savings bank account from banks namely &lt;b style="background-color: #f4cccc;"&gt;Sity Bank&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b style="background-color: #f4cccc;"&gt;Exis Bank&lt;/b&gt;. I had 10,000 bucks in my Exis Bank account and just Rs.4 in my Sity Bank account. Near my locality I did not have any ATM, either of these banks, but I found out an ATM of yet another bank named &lt;b style="background-color: #f4cccc;"&gt;Onion Bank&lt;/b&gt;. Well, I wanted to withdraw the entire 10,000 bucks from my Exis bank account for some need. So I decided to walk into Onion bank ATM. I took out my ATM card from my purse, swiped it through the ATM of Onion bank  and when it prompted me to enter the password, I entered the password. Password got&amp;nbsp; accepted&amp;nbsp; and then I enter the amout for withdrawal and then after sometime, i get a message of failed transaction. I tried it for 3 to 4 times, still the same error, TRANSACTION FAILED !. I thought that Onion bank ATM does not accept my card for some reason and I walked out of the ATM.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span class="fullpost"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;On the way back to my home, I just had a strange feeling for what might be the reason for transaction failure for no specific reason. Later I realized. Did I tell you, which ATM card I used to swipe through the Onion Bank ATM? I guess no. Well to my stuppidness I used the Sity bank ATM card which just had Rs.4 in it. How dumb I am. You must be agreeing to the fact that, yea I how dumb I am&amp;nbsp; for I tried to withdraw 10,000 from an account which just had Rs.4.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_2RdcFsdvQws/SpvtQnE9-pI/AAAAAAAAAxc/Cwk7XDQNaAg/s1600-h/atm.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"&gt;&lt;img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_2RdcFsdvQws/SpvtQnE9-pI/AAAAAAAAAxc/Cwk7XDQNaAg/s320/atm.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;That did not stop me from thinking deeply into that on the way back home. I cant be that dumb, I might have accidentally picked up Sity bank ATM card from my purse. Accidentally picked up my Sity bank card thinking it is Exis bank ATM card...hey hey..that means to withdraw money I must have used the Exis bank password right. Yes, I remember , I used Exis bank password on a wrong&amp;nbsp; ATM card. But then how the hell did the password work out on Sity bank ATM card and provided me with my bank details. This question is still killing me. Is something wrong with the Sity bank ATM system that on its card any random password just worked out. Oh crap this is very bad indeed, or is it something else, if it is what is it??&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Have you ever been in this kind of situation or would like to share with me your ATM funny experince, just leave me a comment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Have a good day :)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1'